🎓 Task 1: Digital Literacy Awareness Resource
Role: Student Digital Ambassador

Objective: Empowering batchmates through visual digital education.

📋 Overview
As the Student Digital Ambassador, I developed this one-page visual resource to simplify the concept of Digital Literacy. In an era where technical fluency is mandatory, this infographic serves as a foundational guide to help students move beyond basic device usage toward critical, safe, and professional digital engagement.

🔍 Key Topics Covered
Digital Literacy Defined: Understanding that being "digitally literate" involves critical thinking, information evaluation, and creative problem-solving.

Safe Internet Practices: A checklist for protecting personal data, recognizing phishing attempts, and maintaining digital privacy.

Professional Online Presence: Tips for building a "future-proof" digital footprint that appeals to recruiters and academic institutions.

🛠️ Methodology
Design Tool: Created using Canva for high-impact visual hierarchy and readability.

Format: Optimized as a single-page infographic for easy sharing via social media and student portals.

This resource aims to bridge the gap between "using technology" and "understanding technology," ensuring our batch is equipped for both academic success and the modern workforce.
